  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators assessed whether short-term cardiac rehabilitation following pacemaker&#xD;
      implantation was enough to improve both physical function and quality of life.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Exercise-based cardiac rehabilitation (CR) improves clinical outcomes in patients with&#xD;
      cardiovascular diseases. However, few data exist regarding the role of early short-term CR in&#xD;
      patients undergoing pacemaker (PM) implantation. The investigators assessed whether&#xD;
      short-term CR following PM implantation was enough to improve both physical function and&#xD;
      quality of life (QOL).&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
